            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Looking at the code, it seems like the state of all the windows *in the current tab* is saved before executing the preview callback [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/29fe883aa9166bdbcae3f935523c75a8aa56fe45/src/nvim/ex_getln.c#L2532). Then, after the preview callback, the previously saved state is restored [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/29fe883aa9166bdbcae3f935523c75a8aa56fe45/src/nvim/ex_getln.c#L2580).\r\n\r\nThe problem is that the `:Test` command is modifying a buffer (in a window) that was not present in the current tab when it's information was saved to be restored later. That's why only the first character shown in the screen is kept after executing `:Test`, when the second character was added to the buffer, the state being saved to be restored later already included the new window with the new buffer containing that first character.",
